<bibRefCitation author="Humes, A. G." box="[596,750,1485,1511]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="609 - 653" refId="ref16443" refString="Humes, A. G. (1996) Deep-sea Copepoda (Siphonostomatoida) from hydrothermal sites on the Mid-Atlantic Ridge at 23 ° and 37 °. Bulletin of Marine Science, 58, 609 - 653." type="journal article" year="1996">Humes, 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Humes, 1996" authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1996" box="[762,1007,1485,1511]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="teres">
<emphasis box="[762,776,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[791,844,1486,1511]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">teres</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Humes, A. G." box="[853,1007,1485,1511]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="609 - 653" refId="ref16443" refString="Humes, A. G. (1996) Deep-sea Copepoda (Siphonostomatoida) from hydrothermal sites on the Mid-Atlantic Ridge at 23 ° and 37 °. Bulletin of Marine Science, 58, 609 - 653." type="journal article" year="1996">Humes, 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Humes, 1987" authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1987" box="[1068,1401,1485,1511]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verruculatus">
<emphasis box="[1068,1082,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1097,1239,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">verruculatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Humes, A. G." box="[1247,1401,1485,1511]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="645 - 788" refId="ref16279" refString="Humes, A. G. (1987) Copepoda from deep-sea hydrothermal vents. Bulletin of Marine Science, 41, 645 - 788." type="journal article" year="1987">Humes, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. In six of these species, at least one of legs 1–4 has an inner seta on the coxa. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1987" box="[1005,1174,1521,1547]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verruculatus">
<emphasis box="[1005,1019,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1032,1174,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">verruculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the remaining species, there is no inner seta on the coxa of any of legs 1–4, which is comparable with 
<taxonomicName authority="Lee &amp; Kim &amp; Kim, 2020" authorityName="Lee &amp; Kim &amp; Kim" authorityYear="2020" box="[1038,1152,1557,1583]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinifer" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1038,1052,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1066,1152,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">spinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1158,1218,1557,1583]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1052,1835]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1987" box="[199,502,1593,1619]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verruculatus">
<emphasis box="[199,502,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Stygiopontius verruculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, known from the East Pacific Rise, was described based only on the male (
<bibRefCitation author="Humes, A. G." pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="645 - 788" refId="ref16279" refString="Humes, A. G. (1987) Copepoda from deep-sea hydrothermal vents. Bulletin of Marine Science, 41, 645 - 788." type="journal article" year="1987">Humes 1987</bibRefCitation>
). Although a direct comparison between it and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lee &amp; Kim &amp; Kim, 2020" authorityName="Lee &amp; Kim &amp; Kim" authorityYear="2020" box="[732,845,1629,1655]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinifer" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[732,746,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[759,845,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">spinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[851,910,1629,1655]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
may be difficult, some sexually non-dimorphic characters may be used to compare male 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1987" box="[618,788,1665,1691]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verruculatus">
<emphasis box="[618,632,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[646,788,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">verruculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and female 
<taxonomicName authority="Lee &amp; Kim &amp; Kim, 2020" authorityName="Lee &amp; Kim &amp; Kim" authorityYear="2020" box="[928,1042,1665,1691]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinifer" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[928,942,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[956,1042,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">spinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1050,1112,1665,1691]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, as follows: (1) the epimeral regions of the fourth pedigerous somite are rounded in 
<taxonomicName authority="Lee &amp; Kim &amp; Kim, 2020" authorityName="Lee &amp; Kim &amp; Kim" authorityYear="2020" box="[765,879,1701,1727]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinifer" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[765,779,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[793,879,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">spinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[885,945,1701,1727]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
but tapering and pointed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1987" box="[1259,1429,1701,1727]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verruculatus">
<emphasis box="[1259,1273,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1287,1429,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">verruculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; (2) the innermost distal seta on the caudal ramus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lee &amp; Kim &amp; Kim, 2020" authorityName="Lee &amp; Kim &amp; Kim" authorityYear="2020" box="[736,851,1737,1763]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinifer" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[736,750,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[765,851,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">spinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[858,918,1737,1763]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is unilaterally pinnate, whereas that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1987" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verruculatus">
<emphasis box="[1363,1377,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">verruculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is naked; and (3) the inner element on the basis of the maxilliped is a seta located at the proximal third in 
<taxonomicName authority="Lee &amp; Kim &amp; Kim, 2020" authorityName="Lee &amp; Kim &amp; Kim" authorityYear="2020" box="[151,265,1809,1835]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinifer" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[151,165,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[179,265,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">spinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[272,332,1809,1835]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
but a ball-like process located near distal third in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humes" authorityYear="1987" box="[891,1061,1809,1835]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Dirivultidae" genus="Stygiopontius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verruculatus">
<emphasis box="[891,905,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[919,1061,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">verruculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
